In a press release on the official Whatsapp blog, the communication giant announced last week that the following devices and platforms will not be supported past this year. These include: BlackBerry, including BlackBerry 10 Nokia S40 Nokia Symbian S60 Android 2.1 and Android 2.2 Windows Phone 7.1According to the company, &#8220;While these mobile devices have been an important part of our story, they don&#8217;t offer the kind of capabilities we need to expand our app&#8217;s features in the future.&#8221;They appealed to users of these devices to opt for an upgrade to a Android, iPhone, or Windows Phone before the end of this year to ensure Whatsapp support.